<p>That's it! Run Composer update again:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">composer update</div></code></pre>
<p>We <em>may</em> get another error about <em>another</em> library, but this is the process: run
<code>$ composer update</code>, find the problematic package, update its version and repeat.</p>
<p>Yep: another problem. This time it's from <code>sensio/generator-bundle</code>. Go back to
Packagist: the version in the Standard Edition is <code>^3.0</code>. Update our <code>composer.json</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="33b8814e0e">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
