<p>And run Composer again:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">composer update</div></code></pre>
<p>If you get an error from a package that's <em>not</em> part of the Standard Edition, 
then you'll need to go look up that library in Packagist or on GitHub to find
a version that's 3.0-compatible. That's exactly what we did with AsseticBundle.</p>
<p>Et voila! We just downloaded Symfony 3.0.8.</p>
<p>Well, let's see if it works! Refresh! Yes! Everything looks great: a major framework
upgrade <em>without</em> breaking your code! Give yourself a congrats. And then, don't forget
to run your tests and QA your site to make sure we didn't missing anything.</p>
<p>All right, guys, if you have any questions, let me know.</p>
<p>Seeya next time!</p>

    
